Data management




Cookies policy




This cookies policy outlines how the information collected on this website is handled. 
Cookies
All the websites of the Edmond de Rothschild Group and its subsidiaries use cookies for statistical purposes and to improve the experience of its users. One kind of cookie that we use (a technical cookie) is essential to improve your browser experience (e.g.: to avoid having to identify yourself each time you login).
What is a cookie?
Cookies are files which are stored on your computer to keep track of your visits to the website and your preferences as you move between pages. Sometimes they are used to save settings between visits. Cookies allow statistics to be gathered about how users view website content in order to enhance its functionality and its user-friendliness.
How are cookies used on this website?
The cookies we store on the websites of the Edmond de Rothschild Group and its subsidiaries are used to:
gather anonymous statistics concerning website visits and visitors as well as its pages so that we can determine which parts of the website are working well and which need to be improved
to improve the speed and performance of the website pages
Deleting or modifying cookies
You may decline the cookies set by the website at any time by deleting them. This can be done via the settings of your Internet browser.




































	
